rComments: Probably the most boring professor I've ever had. He makes the class difficult by giving awful lectures, 4 major assignments, weekly online assignments, and random pop quizzes. This class is time consuming and terribly given. He is definitely a really nice person, but he's not good at teaching.
teacherRatingTags: ['So many papers', 'Beware of pop quizzes', 'Tough grader']

rComments: This prof makes things harder than what they are. The exam is 60% of total grade and for the other 40% you need to do 3 assignments and 2 projects and for each of them you need to spend at least 15h!!!! About the required book for this class, its the worst book written in english I think. Dont buy it.

In this class, there is no midterm. Several long assignments which are easy to get high grades. The practice finals are impossible to answer until you do a practice in class. Final is worth 70% of the final grade. Part of the class is not in the posted slides but done on the board. ARIMA is still a very mysterious, just like the rules at crickets

Never went to class, pulled a 90 on the midterm.  No need to go to class if you have a good work ethic. Assignments were sort of tough. Do practice mid-terms, read the textbook and watch youtube explanations if you want to do well. His lectures are unbearable, you won't want to pay attention because he goes through multiple topics fast.
Pretty nice prof, but his lecture makes me sleepy. I cannot focus on when he was lecturing. Study by yourself, then you will pass.

Overall, he gave good feedback and help for assignments. His lectures were okay, but focused more on theory than actually doing the problems out. Very few examples given in lectures. Boring class, but because the content is boring.

I found this course really interesting and I learned a lot from it. The course isn't easy. It is possible to do well but you will have to work for it by doing some extra research on topics covered in class because the professors notes are not the clearest. The professor is really nice and can be helpful if you ask him specific questions.
Prof is very smart, but cannot explain the material properly. For these reasons, the lectures are very long.
Sitting through a 3 hour lecture was extremely difficult... Ended up teaching myself material through his slides and the textbook.

Excellent professor! Clear lecturer, works hard to teach stats. Don't expect to ace a stats course without hard work though. Go to class, office hours, and work hard and you will learn stats with Quon.

He is a nice guy but the course is really brutal and hard.  However he seems to want to help you succeed but he will not budge on grading and his lectures are so dull.  I found this course really hard cause my math skills are not fantastic but overall I think Quon is a fair professor.

He's a very nice person and takes the time to explain to you. However, he doesn't explain it very well in class and makes it a little confusing. Stats2 is a very time consuming class and very tough. Try putting everything on cheat sheet for exams.

Good prof! His powerpoints give examples that are very abstract which might be hard to undertand for those who can't see the solution quickly. Exams and assignments closely reflect what was taught in class. He's very nice and will always try to make sure that everyone passes the class since stats is hard to understand.
Toughhhhh class.  But prof quon is a fair gentleman, helps out those you show up !! :)

Dr. Quon is an excellent teacher.  Very smart and wants his students to do well. Puts in a lot of effort with office hours, responding to emails, etc, but you need to put in the effort too bc stats isn't easy!!  Go to Class and work hard and Quon will take of you.

Highly recommended prof! stats is a pain in the ass..but don't blame the prof for that.  Quon is very approachable, will answer all questions in class, office hrs or by email and he's very punctual when it comes to putting up grades

You might curse him in the beginning for making things ultra confusing. Just ignore his teaching method and study from the text book and Mystat lab exercises -- you'll manage to get an A+ easily! I'd also advice to attend Michael Sinclair's review sessions, they are very helpful!(But don't just rely on them, sum effort on your side is also required

LISTEN - everyone saying hes bad or not interested or rude is WRONG. hes sincere and the issue is hes TOO good at stats. He isnt able to dumb it down for students alot of the times but use your book, dgd and read his notes and theres NO reason you cant do well..Quon haters are people who did nothing with their time and did not try
Try and avoid him for 3 hour lectures. He doesn't do the best job of communicating subject matter in class but is very helpful if you approach him with clear questions. Bell-curved midterm&final...

Quon may go above and beyond at times, but he makes a sincere effort to convey the matter effectively.  Go to his office hours, e-mail him questions, and post questions about assignments on the forum. He answers questions with questions when you aren't clear enough. Be absolutely precise and specific and he'll likely give you a proper answer!
Terrible prof. Always makes things way more complicated than they should be. And he hates asians
He cares about his students. He is very dedicated.

Stay away if you want to get a high mark. but if you want to get a deeper understanding of stats theory, he is fairly good. you would find his lecture not highly relevant to the exam. I think that's why most people find his class hard. But i learned a lot in his class. He know his stuff.
I learnt nothing in this class.. I taught myself!
No Comments

Means well, but is too smart to teach stats2. Makes simple things way too complicated. I attended all classes, failed the midterm, but went to see a tutor (Ibrahim Ozer)the day before the final and he taught me the entire course in 2 hours and I got an A on the final. Quon means well and knows his stuff, but not suitable for teaching basic stats.

The Professor, who is a very nice guy, knows the content well but often complicates things... but don't freak out if you're lost. The DGDs are a LIFE SAVER, I strongly urge you to go. Its not a difficult course but you really have to teach yourself so be ready to put in some time for it.

Very boring lecturer!  His voice is very monotonous and he doesn't really take the time to give his students tips for solving problems (students with other profs were given loads of tips).  Answers students' questions horribly and fails to cover exam material in class.  All things considered, I preferred Nash (yikes, can't believe I'm saying that).
Very BORING. Has no relationship to real world. I have a math background and he even confused me (Others had no clue). Not fit to teach graduate level courses.
Can u say DULL...........
Incompetent. Rude. Direspectful. Incapable of teaching.

Don't listen to all the idiots on this site. He is a great prof. You just have to pay attention to his lecture and you will do well. These other retards probably didn't pay attention and that's why they failed and now they trying to blame it on Quon.

One of the worst profs I have ever met.  In 2001 failed 17% of the class he taught in 2003 – 12% just by examining areas he never bothered to cover in class.  Never answered a question when asked – always was giving some canny, smart-ass blurb. Fortunatel

Terrible prof, perhaps the worst prof the department ever had. Makes no effort to teach, has no interest in what he is doing, and what he is paid for, and will test on exam what he has not taught in the class.
Great teacher if you like falling asleep in class
Not a motivational speaker, but comprehensive and fair.  Good person to ask deeper questions - not just the normal "how do I do...."
He is the worst Prof in the world, he can't teach a thing.
TERRIBLE.  He makes no effort to make the course interesting.  His lectures do not focus on what we will be tested on. Again...TERRIBLE
